&lt;h1&gt;Talk Slides&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Definition&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Volcano - Take a small issue in git and have it erupt into a massive issue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Example 1&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;WHAT YOU SHOULD NEVER DO&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;quot;Me: Now to add these 2 days of code to GitHub.&lt;br&gt;&lt;code&gt;git add .&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br&gt;whoops I added environment vars lets just revert...&amp;quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2 days of work &lt;a href=&#34;https://t.co/346grNXfUz&#34;&gt;pic.twitter.com/346grNXfUz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Jay Miller - #BlackLivesMatter (@kjaymiller) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/kjaymiller/status/1350241433836351489?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;January 16, 2021&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt; &lt;script async src=&#34;https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js&#34; charset=&#34;utf-8&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;How to solve this problem&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[.column]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;If you pushed to github.&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sorry gonna have to delete that repo in GH. To really clean the history.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[.column]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;If you didn&#39;t...&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;codehilite&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;rm -rf .git
git init
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Example 2&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;Who just spent the last 3 hours trying to squash a commit (I accidentally uploaded some CSV files and it&amp;#39;s making the pulls take much longer and they are unnecessary)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The same person that couldn&amp;#39;t get it to work. That person.. &lt;a href=&#34;https://t.co/ezIIlCYJmw&#34;&gt;pic.twitter.com/ezIIlCYJmw&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Jay Miller - #BlackLivesMatter (@kjaymiller) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/kjaymiller/status/1338591508048408576?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;December 14, 2020&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt; &lt;script async src=&#34;https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js&#34; charset=&#34;utf-8&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;via @anthonypjshaw&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;git rebase -i

commit hash before the one you want to drop
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preventative Measures&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;DON&#39;T LOAD EVERYTHING AT ONCE&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;git commit &amp;lt;filenames&amp;gt; -m &#39;update to specific piece of code&#39;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bonus Points to IDEs
- Tower
- GitHub
- PyCharm
- VSCode&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Before Doing Anything âš ï¸&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;git template or git script&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;codehilite&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code&gt;npx gitignore python
&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; .envrc &amp;gt;&amp;gt; .gitignore
&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; node_modules &amp;gt;&amp;gt; .gitignore
&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; *.json *.csv &amp;gt;&amp;gt; .gitignore
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

