&lt;p&gt;This is a post mostly for archival purposes but today I renamed the diversityorgs project to Tech Diversity Orgs and moved the domain to &lt;a href=&#34;https://techdiversityorgs.com&#34;&gt;https://techdiversityorgs.com&lt;/a&gt;. The reason why is simple, cost.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;em&gt;.tech&lt;/em&gt; domain is &lt;strong&gt;$50&lt;/strong&gt; to renew and the &lt;em&gt;.com&lt;/em&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;$15&lt;/strong&gt;. This doesn&#39;t seem like much in the grand scheme of things but you have to remember that TDO doesn&#39;t make money. This move &lt;strong&gt;cuts the annual cost by about 40%&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tally:&lt;/strong&gt;
- Server Fees: $60/year
- Domain: &lt;strike&gt;$50&lt;/strike&gt; $15&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I do see a couple opportunities to save but at the moment having a dedicated server makes this project a bit more &lt;em&gt;production-level&lt;/em&gt;. In the future I could see parts of this project evolving over time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also you may find a bug or missed area. My bad just let me know on the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/kjaymiller/diversity-orgs-tech&#34;&gt;github repo&lt;/a&gt; (still under the original project name)&lt;/p&gt;

